<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9836> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9836" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/23> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "pp. 65-72" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8454> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8454" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 730" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7836> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7836" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 189. Procos. 187. In MRR 1.369, refer also to Macrob. Sat. 1.12.16; cf. Ovid Fasti 6.812. See Janne, RBPh 12, 1933, 515-531.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2472> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2472" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 456f. These two enemies became publicly reconciled upon being elected (Liv. 40.45.6-46.16; Cic. Prov. Cons. 20; Val. Max. 4.2.1; Gell. 12.8.5-6; cf. Varro in Fest. 358 L, app. crit.). They instituted taxes and made changes in the tribal assembly (Liv. 40.51.9). Their building activity was notable, and especially the Basilica Aemilia et Fulvia in the Forum (Varro LL 6.4; Liv. 40.46.16, and 51-52; cf. Grueber, CRRBM 2.291; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1.193ff.; Plut. Caes. 29.3). They appointed Lepidus Princeps Senatus (Liv. 40.51.1). See also Cato in FOR 1.189; Cic. De Or. 2.287." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2303> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2303" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Greece, whence he returned to celebrate his triumph over the Aetolians and Cephallenians (Cic. Mur. 31; Liv. 38.42-44; 39.4-5; 40.45.6; Act. Tr., Degrassi 80f., 554; Auct. Vir. Ill. 52.2; Eutrop. 4.5, in 186). With his booty he built and decorated the temple of Hercules and the Muses (Cic. Arch. 27; Plin. NH 35.66; Eumen. Panegyr. 4.7; cf. CIL 1\n     .2.615, 616- ILS 17; Polyb. 21.30.9-10; Serv. ad Aen. 1.8; also Grueber, CRRBM 1.441f.; Cesano, Stud. Num. 1 [1942] 189). He gave special games in 186 (Liv. 39.22.1-4; Cassiod.)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2280> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2280" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His imperium prorogued for a year (Liv. 38.35.3), he completed the capture of Cephallenia, and intervened in the Peloponnese between Sparta and the Achaean League (Liv. 38.29-34; Polyb. 21.32.b and c; Flor. 1.25.4; Zon. 9.21)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2235> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2235" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 37.47.7, and 48.1; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 454f.; Vell. 1.15.2; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Zon. 9.19-20; and on Fulvius, CIL 1\n     .2.615, 616- ILS 16, 17; Polyb. 21.27.1; on Manlius, Polyb. 21.24.9. Fulvius was assigned the Aetolian war, with instructions also to attack Cephallenia and to hold the elections in Rome (Liv. 37.50.5-8). He besieged Ambracia and negotiated the peace with the Aetolians (Liv. 38.3-10; cf. Polyb. 21.25-31; Flor. 1.25; Polyaen. 6.17; Auct. Vir. Ill. 52; Zon. 9.21), besieged Same of Cephallenia (Liv. 38.28.5-29; Polyb. 21.32; Zon. 9.21), and returned to Rome, apparently during the siege, to hold the elections (Liv. 38.35.1; cf. Holleaux, BCH 54 [1930] 1-41).\n     \n      1\n     \n     Manlius succeeded Scipio in Asia (Liv. 37.50.2-3 and 8, and 60.1), where he led an expedition into the interior to subdue the Gauls (Polyb. 21.33-39; Diod. 29.12-13; Liv. 38.12-27; cf. Claud. fr. 66 Peter; Val. Ant. fr. 44 Peter; Nep. Hann. 13.2; Trog. Prol. 32; Val. Max. 6.1, ext. 2; Flor. 1.27; App. Syr. 39, and 42; Auct. Vir. Ill. 55; Ruf. Fest. Brev. 11.2; Oros. 4.20.25; Zon. 9.20). He too made offerings at Delos (I. de Délos 442 B, 100; 1429 A, 25; 1441 A, 107; 1450 A, 67)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2181> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2181" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Farther Spain (Liv. 36.2.8; Act. Tr., Degrassi 78f., 553; Auct. Vir. Ill. 52), until succeeded by Aemilius, when he returned to celebrate an ovatio (Liv. 36.21.10-11; Act. Tr.; Auct. Vir. Ill. 52; cf. Oros. 4.20.19)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2159> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2159" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His imperium prorogued in Farther Spain (Liv. 35.20.11), he won important victories as Proconsul (Liv. 35.22.5; cf. Act. Tr. for 191) over the Oretani and Vettones (Liv. 35.22.6-8; Oros. 4.20.16 and 19)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2124> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2124" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Victorious over the Vaccaei and other tribes (Liv. 35.7.8; Oros. 4.20.16 and 19)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2120> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2120" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elections: Liv. 34.54.2 Provinces and armies Liv. 34.55.6, and 56.9." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2031> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2031" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 33.42.8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10098> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10098" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Aetoleis et Cephallenia. MRR I.369, Itgenshorst no. 180, Rich no. 179." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10097> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10097" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Ovation ex Hispania Ulteriore. MRR I.354, Itgenshorst no. 174, Rich no. 173." .
